From d0b69255361b56487bc50434c0c91335d27bc323 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Your Name <you@example.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 13:57:23 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/5] feat(wallet): password-encrypted storage + key/mnemonic
 import-export

Implements the `// TODO: Use password for storage encryption`:

- Encrypt persistent storage at rest: Argon2id(password) -> AES-256-GCM
  envelope (new src/crypto.rs). Wrong password fails cleanly. Empty
  password keeps legacy plaintext, so the FFI and existing wallets are
  unaffected; new CLI wallets created with a password are encrypted.
- Gate all CLI commands on the password (read once, decrypt on load,
  re-encrypt on save). restore-keys rebuilds without the old password.
- Persist the recovery phrase inside the encrypted store so it can be
  re-exported.
- New `account` subcommands: export-mnemonic, export-key (public signing
  key, hex), import-key (add a public account from a raw key).
- Move the password/phrase prompts to stderr so stdout stays clean for
  machine consumers (the GUI module).
